page.title: 01LANDSCAPE WALTON HOLT
page.content: This area is wholly agricultural land - overall mainly grassland. There are two very small areas of non-coniferous woodland. The height above sea level varies from 133 metres to 173 metres. There are two tributary streams of the River Swift running West through the sector. The A50 road runs North/South through the Eastern edge of the sector. The B5414 runs South West off the A 50 towards North Kilworth. There are two minor roads interspersed by five public footpaths and one bridleway.
